#* {{quote-book|en|year=2001|author=James G. Lennox|title=Aristotle's Philosophy of Biology|page=151|passage=Terms like 'house', 'sphere', 'animal', and 'human' do not refer to other '''thises''' distinct from these ones here &mdash; they refer to the sort of thing these ones here are.}}
